                     <interp inst="t17850112-27-person387" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am round house keeper of St. Giles's, I only know the people brought this charge to me, and told me the same story.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I follow the market, I had been out with some fish, and saw a mob under the gateway, and two women were running along and they shoved me down, and the watchman came and took hold of me, I said to the watchman, I know this woman and her brother.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17850112-27-verdict152" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17850112-27-verdict152" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>, <rs id="t17850112-27-punish153" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17850112-27-punish153" type="punishmentCategory" value="death"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t17850112-27-defend379 t17850112-27-punish153"></join>
               Death
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>Tried by the first Middlesex Jury before Mr. Baron HOTHAM.</p>
